caseFileID.description: CaseFile ID obtained from DU submissions.

pdaSubmitterEntity.description: Name of entity making the property data submission.

propertyDataCollectorName.description: Name of the individual who conducted the property data collection.

stateCredentialID.description: If the data collector is an appraiser or appraiser trainee, the license or certification number of the appraiser must be provided.

licenseState.description: If the data collector is an appraiser or appraiser trainee, the state of the appraiser's license or certification must be provided.

licenseExpiration.description: If the data collector is an appraiser or appraiser trainee, the date on which their license or certification expires must be provided.

propertyDataCollectorType.description:
Name of the labor force type of the individual who conducted the property data collection.

Developer Note: This field must be auto-populated by the fulfillment vendor.

inspectionType.description: Select the best option to describes the type of inspection performed at the property.

latitude.description: Waterfall Subject Latitude as centroid of latitude of all images, OR a specific image likely to be present in all dwellings, such as the kitchen OR a photo of the main entrance of the dwelling. If latitude from images is unavailable, use geocoder from subject address.

longitude.description: Waterfall Subject Longitude as centroid of longitude of all images, OR a specific image likely to be present in all dwellings, such as the kitchen OR a photo of the main entrance of the dwelling. If latitude/longitude from images is unavailable, use geocoder from subject address.

latitude.description: latitude coming from prepopulated invision Coordinates.

longitude.description: longitude coming from prepopulated invision Coordinates

unitFee.description: User to provide the home owners association fee that is due either monthly or annually.

roomName.description:
User to select the best option to identify the room. 

A bedroom is defined as having a window, closet, and door that can be closed. The bedroom should have two means of egress, i.e. the door and window.

description.description: User to enter free form text to describe the type of room when room type of 'OTHER_ROOM' is selected. The acceptable string length is 100 characters or less.

cv_propertyDataCollectorUserType.description: Type of the the data collector.

userId.description: User Identifier of the party associated with the inspection report.

roleType.description: Select the best option that describes the role of the party in the inspection report.

firstName.description: First name of the party associated with the inspection report.

lastName.description: Last name of the party associated with the inspection report.

companyName.description: Company name of the party associated with the inspection report.

streetAddress.description: The street address of the party associated with the inspection report.

city.description: The city name where the associated party is located.

state.description: The state where the associated party is located.

postalCode.description: The postal code where the associated party is located.

phone.description: The phone number of the associated party.

email.description: The email address of the associated party.

inspectionType.description: Select the best option to describes the type of inspection performed at the property.

inspectionDate.description: The date that the property inspection was performed.

signatureDate.description: The date that the inspection report was signed by the party.

credentialType.description: Select the best option to describes the type of professional credentials that the party holds.

credentialId.description: The ID of the professional credentials held by the party role.

credentialState.description: The ID number of the professional credentials held by the party role.

credentialExpDate.description: The expiration date of the role's professional credentials.
